@page
@model Bagrot_HTML.Pages.HomeModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Home page";
}
<link href="~/css/stylesheet.css" rel="stylesheet" />


<main>
    <header>
        <h1 style="font-size:3vw" class="pageTitle">Home</h1>
        <hr />
    </header>
    <div class="box">
        <h2>Welcome</h2>
        <p>
            Learn more about <a asp-page="/Carbohydrates and Sugar">carbohydrates</a> and how to read <a asp-page="/food labels">food labels</a> to make informed food choices.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="box">
        <h2>Why Are Carbohydrates Important?</h2>
        <p>Carbohydrates are the body's most important and readily available source of energy. They help fuel the brain, kidneys, heart muscles, and central nervous system.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="box">
        <h2>Types of Carbohydrates</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Simple Carbohydrates:</strong> Found in fruits, milk, and sugar-sweetened products.</li>
            <li><strong>Complex Carbohydrates:</strong> Found in whole grains, vegetables, and legumes.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="box">
        <h2>Good vs. Bad Carbs</h2>
        <p>Healthy carbohydrate sources include whole grains, fruits, and vegetables. Avoid refined carbs such as white bread, sugary cereals, and soda.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="box">
        <h2>Health Benefits of Carbohydrates</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Provide energy for daily activities.</li>
            <li>Support brain function and cognitive performance.</li>
            <li>Help with digestion through fiber-rich sources.</li>
            <li>Reduce the risk of heart disease and diabetes when chosen wisely.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="box">
        <h2>How to Make Healthier Choices</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Choose whole grains over refined grains.</li>
            <li>Limit added sugars in your diet.</li>
            <li>Read nutrition labels carefully.</li>
            <li>Incorporate more fiber-rich foods.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="box">
        <h2>Carbohydrates and Blood Sugar</h2>
        <p>Refined carbohydrates can cause rapid spikes in blood sugar levels, increasing the risk of diabetes. Whole grains and fiber-rich foods help maintain steady blood sugar levels.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="box">
        <h2>Daily Carbohydrate Intake</h2>
        <p>Experts recommend that 50-60% of daily calories come from carbohydrates, with an emphasis on whole grains, fruits, and vegetables.</p>
    </div>
</main>